title: NASA adds asteroid flyby to Lucy mission
summary: NASA has added another asteroid flyby to its Lucy mission later this year that will provide a test of its capabilities for future encounters.

title: NEO Surveyor launch delayed despite funding boost
summary: While Congress provided more funding than NASA requested for an asteroid mission, agency officials said it will not prevent a two-year slip in its launch.

title: SpaceX launches 56 more Starlink satellites from Cape Canaveral
summary: Another batch of 56 Starlink satellites rocketed into orbit from Cape Canaveral before dawn Thursday aboard a Falcon 9 launcher, continuing the deployment of SpaceX’s second-generation internet constellation begun last month. Liftoff occurred at 4:32 a.m. EST (0922 GMT).

title: Lamborn named chair of House Armed Services strategic forces subcommittee
summary: Rep. Doug Lamborn, a Republican representing Colorado Springs, was named chairman of the House Armed Services Committee’s strategic forces subcommittee.

title: NASA Awards Innovations, Partnership Support Services Agreements
summary: NASA has selected six companies to provide early-stage innovations and partnership support services. The services will be provided across multiple NASA centers. The place of performance will be specified in each specific call, with much of the work being performed virtually.
